                <head>38. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On February 11, <persName corresp="#p_RAAW1">Radford</persName> sent a memorandum
                    from the Joint Chiefs of Staff to the Secretary of Defense recommending concepts
                    and broad outline plans for the use of United States military power under the
                    Manila Pact in the event of Communist aggression in Southeast Asia. For the
                    text, see <hi rend="italic">United States–Vietnam Relations, 1945–1967</hi>,
                    Book 10, pages 885–887.</p>
            </div>
